address: Xã Khánh Phú, Huyện Yên Khánh, Tỉnh Ninh Bình
thought:
**My Analysis of the Administrative Restructuring in Ninh Bình Province**

Okay, so the user wants the new administrative unit for "Xã Khánh Phú, Huyện Yên Khánh, Tỉnh Ninh Bình." My starting point is always to break down the old address: province, district, and ward. I've got "Tỉnh Ninh Bình" (province) and "Xã Khánh Phú" (ward). Now, the real work begins – diving into these resolutions.

First, I checked the overarching provincial resolutions (60-NQ/TW), but it was straightforward: Ninh Bình stayed Ninh Bình after a merger, no changes there.

Then I dug into the more specific resolutions (1654, 1656, 1667 – quickly dismissed those, wrong provinces).  Bingo! 1674/NQ-UBTVQH15, the Ninh Bình resolution.  I had to meticulously read through it. Initially, I saw some confusing mentions of "Xã Yên Khánh" – looked like some restructuring happening around that area, but not what I was looking for.

I zeroed in on line 125, and there it was: **"Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quyô dân số của phường Ninh Phúc và các xã Khánh Hòa, Khánh Phú, Khánh An thành phường mới có tên gọi là phường Đông Hoa Lư."**  *That's it!* "Xã Khánh Phú" is being merged into "phường Đông Hoa Lư".

To confirm, I double-checked the "New Wards" list. And there it was:  {"ward_code":"14566","ward_name":"Phường Đông Hoa Lư","province_name":"Tỉnh Ninh Bình"}.  Everything lines up: the province is consistent, and I've got the new ward name and code.

So, the answer is "Phường Đông Hoa Lư" with code 14566, in "Tỉnh Ninh Bình".  I'm very confident in this one; the resolution was crystal clear, with "Xã Khánh Phú" explicitly mentioned in the merge.  Case closed!
